WEBVTT

00:06.000 --> 00:12.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

00:49.132 --> 00:50.633
(THUNDER CRACKLING)

00:52.719 --> 00:54.220
(MAN PANTING)

01:28.297 --> 01:29.798
(GRUNTS)

01:30.924 --> 01:32.425
(CHOKING)

01:36.680 --> 01:38.602
(LEPRECHAUN LAUGHING)

01:45.022 --> 01:48.091
Scream as you may,
scream as you might,

01:48.191 --> 01:53.430
if you try to escape, you'll be
dead on this night. (LAUGHS)

01:53.530 --> 01:55.182
Curse you.

01:55.282 --> 01:58.501
I'd rather be dead than your slave.

02:01.163 --> 02:02.147
(GASPS)

02:02.247 --> 02:03.748
(PANTING)

02:05.042 --> 02:06.543
(CHUCKLES)

02:07.210 --> 02:10.338
Oh, William, foolish William.

02:11.381 --> 02:13.303
Your shoes are filthy.

02:14.635 --> 02:16.870
Yeah, what trick is this, now?

02:16.970 --> 02:18.997
Don't you know what day it is?

02:19.097 --> 02:22.543
It's a day like any other, since I
tried to take your damn pot of gold.

02:22.643 --> 02:24.419
It's the 17th of March,

02:24.519 --> 02:27.363
the feast of St-Patrick.

02:27.522 --> 02:28.507
And your birthday.

02:28.607 --> 02:32.302
Ah! 'Tis a special
birthday for a leprechaun.

02:32.402 --> 02:34.429
I'm 1,000 years old.

02:34.529 --> 02:38.784
Tonight, I can claim my bride.

02:43.789 --> 02:45.732
Who'd marry a creature like you?

02:45.832 --> 02:48.527
Wait till you gaze
upon this lovely lass.

02:48.627 --> 02:51.655
Her lips so soft, her face so fair,

02:51.755 --> 02:53.824
her bosom so ample. (CHUCKLES)

02:53.924 --> 02:55.492
She's a fit match for me.

02:55.592 --> 02:57.869
And what evil trick will
you use to woo her?

02:57.969 --> 02:59.037
LEPRECHAUN: Tis simple.

02:59.137 --> 03:01.707
She sneezes once, she sneezes twice,

03:01.807 --> 03:05.127
she'll be my bride when
she sneezes thrice.

03:05.227 --> 03:06.920
Sneezes three times?

03:07.020 --> 03:09.172
Ah! And if no one saves her soul,

03:09.272 --> 03:13.427
by speaking "God bless you,"
the fair maiden is mine forever.

03:13.527 --> 03:16.096
And am I to be her slave as well?

03:16.196 --> 03:17.472
Oh, no.

03:17.572 --> 03:22.748
The moment the lassie's married to me,
then you, my slave, shall be set free.

03:22.953 --> 03:24.730
You'd like your freedom,
wouldn't you, William?

03:24.830 --> 03:27.941
You know nothing is more
precious to me than freedom.

03:28.041 --> 03:29.963
But why should I believe you?

03:30.627 --> 03:33.322
By the sacred vow of the wee people.

03:33.422 --> 03:36.550
When I am wed,
you'll have your freedom.

03:48.353 --> 03:49.854
Ah!

03:50.313 --> 03:53.487
Behold, my chosen bride.

03:54.735 --> 03:56.553
WILLIAM: May your wedding be blessed.

03:56.653 --> 04:01.249
And I'd thrash any soul who
dared try and stop this union.

04:09.624 --> 04:11.234
Oh, please, master, no.

04:11.334 --> 04:12.402
What troubles you?

04:12.502 --> 04:14.905
Is she not beautiful enough for me?

04:15.005 --> 04:17.531
The girl, she's my daughter.

04:17.632 --> 04:21.386
Oh, really. Then we
are to be related.

04:23.680 --> 04:25.181
(SNEEZES)

04:33.690 --> 04:35.425
Please, master.

04:35.525 --> 04:36.593
I swear,

04:36.693 --> 04:40.222
I'll find you a score of
lasses fairer than she.

04:40.322 --> 04:41.598
Oh, don't worry.

04:41.698 --> 04:45.543
I'll be gentle with her
on our wedding night.

04:46.953 --> 04:51.879
Now, just one more sneeze,
and you'll have your precious freedom.

04:59.216 --> 05:00.717
(SNEEZES)

05:00.967 --> 05:03.561
God bless you, my child.

05:09.351 --> 05:10.852
(GRUNTS)

05:11.228 --> 05:12.729
(CHOKING)

05:17.526 --> 05:19.369
(WILLIAM STRUGGLING)

05:20.987 --> 05:23.348
You pathetic fool.

05:23.448 --> 05:25.600
You thought you could outsmart me,

05:25.700 --> 05:27.873
the genius of Killarney.

05:28.328 --> 05:31.940
A curse be placed upon your
seed when you go dead.

05:32.040 --> 05:34.067
You may have saved your daughter,

05:34.167 --> 05:36.486
but on my next thousandth birthday

05:36.586 --> 05:41.575
I'll stalk your fairest offspring
and claim her as my bride. (LAUGHS)

05:41.675 --> 05:42.951
(CHOKING)

05:43.051 --> 05:45.599
Happy St-Patrick's Day.

05:49.558 --> 05:51.275
- (GASPS)
- (LEPRECHAUN LAUGHING)

05:57.023 --> 05:58.524
(PANTING)

06:00.652 --> 06:02.199
(SCREAMING)

08:19.040 --> 08:20.901
<i>LEPRECHAUN: Soon.</i>

08:21.001 --> 08:22.986
<i>Soon, my dear.</i>

08:23.086 --> 08:26.055
<i>It's almost time.</i>

08:28.216 --> 08:29.717
(CARS HONKING)

08:48.945 --> 08:51.306
Trust me, this tour is incredible.

08:51.406 --> 08:52.849
You won't believe your eyes.

08:52.949 --> 08:57.020
It will be the most frightening
experience of your life.

08:57.120 --> 08:59.272
Is it really scary?

08:59.372 --> 09:01.858
Let me put it this way,
you're not pregnant are you?

09:01.958 --> 09:03.777
Because our insurance won't cover us.

09:03.877 --> 09:05.153
- (LAUGHING)
- We've had our problems.

09:05.253 --> 09:08.198
Heart conditions, emotionally
unstable or suggestible,

09:08.298 --> 09:10.200
please stay away.

09:10.300 --> 09:12.285
This is not the tour for you.

09:12.385 --> 09:14.537
Let's go, this is one
of those rip-offs.

09:14.637 --> 09:17.332
Sure, walk away, I understand.

09:17.432 --> 09:20.543
If hearing the actual sound
of Jayne Mansfield's head

09:20.643 --> 09:22.963
being severed from her body
is too intense for you,

09:23.063 --> 09:26.112
well, then, you know,
more power to you.

09:27.150 --> 09:30.470
Maybe you should try Disneyland.
It's probably more your speed.

09:30.570 --> 09:32.055
Now, listen sport,
are you saying that...

09:32.155 --> 09:33.723
I'm not saying anything.

09:33.823 --> 09:36.017
This tour's too much for most people.

09:36.117 --> 09:37.227
Now, if you'll excuse me.

09:37.327 --> 09:38.953
You, sir.

09:39.662 --> 09:43.274
Are you interested in the
uncut, uncensored truth

09:43.374 --> 09:45.318
about Hollywood's dark side?

09:45.418 --> 09:47.988
Hey, honey, didn't we see this the
other night on A Current Event?

09:48.088 --> 09:49.197
No, sir, you did not.

09:49.297 --> 09:52.409
This is the stuff the TV networks
just don't have the guts to show.

09:52.509 --> 09:54.869
I wanna go and you're too scared.

09:54.969 --> 09:57.247
You can just meet
me back at the hotel.

09:57.347 --> 10:01.042
Step right in, madam, there's a
window seat reserved just for you.

10:01.142 --> 10:02.627
I am not scared.

10:02.727 --> 10:07.698
You can wait for her at this really cute
ice cream parlor right down the block.

10:07.982 --> 10:09.009
Give me two tickets.

10:09.109 --> 10:12.613
Now there's a brave man.
You won't be sorry.

10:15.073 --> 10:16.433
Hey.

10:16.533 --> 10:19.206
An award-winning performance.
(LAUGHS)

10:19.327 --> 10:20.353
Can we get away, now?

10:20.453 --> 10:21.604
Bridget, I'll be just a minute,

10:21.704 --> 10:23.898
let me just get these last two
suckers and I'm all yours, okay?

10:23.998 --> 10:27.402
I understand. How can I compete with
Jayne Mansfield's severed head?

10:27.502 --> 10:29.128
- Well, you can't.
- (LAUGHS)

10:30.088 --> 10:32.907
You folks are in luck.
We've just had two cancellations.

10:33.007 --> 10:36.494
Better grab these now, our next
opening isn't until December.

10:36.594 --> 10:37.704
Wow!

10:37.804 --> 10:39.247
Looks like our lucky day, huh?

10:39.347 --> 10:41.082
All right, sure.

10:41.182 --> 10:43.126
- And there you go, okay.
- Great.

10:43.226 --> 10:47.071
Down that way, right around the
back, there, yup, there you are.

10:47.564 --> 10:48.548
Hop in.

10:48.648 --> 10:51.676
Right into the deluxe
observation chamber.

10:51.776 --> 10:53.261
Be prepared, everybody.

10:53.361 --> 10:55.805
I will now summon your
guide to the dark side.

10:55.905 --> 10:58.533
Mortimer, the all-knowing.

11:02.745 --> 11:05.148
All loaded in.

11:05.248 --> 11:09.069
Now it's just you, me, and a ton of hot
steel going two hundred miles an hour.

11:09.169 --> 11:12.906
Cody, we're going to the go-kart
park, not the Indy 500.

11:13.006 --> 11:14.657
A boy can dream, can't he?

11:14.757 --> 11:17.744
I can't believe we're actually gonna
spend the afternoon together.

11:17.844 --> 11:19.788
Listen, this job's important.

11:19.888 --> 11:22.791
I gotta make enough money to
pay for my sister's eye operation.

11:22.891 --> 11:24.959
Good plan. If only you had a sister.

11:25.059 --> 11:27.128
Oh, you know me too well.

11:27.228 --> 11:28.963
- Let's go nab your uncle and split.
- Okay.

11:29.063 --> 11:30.780
Okay.

11:32.317 --> 11:34.319
- (CHUCKLING)
- Morty!

11:35.486 --> 11:37.847
Well, I'm glad to see you
guys got that cleaning lady.

11:37.947 --> 11:39.699
Hey, Morty!

11:41.284 --> 11:44.287
He's not under the shirts.

11:44.829 --> 11:46.626
I know where he is.

11:48.666 --> 11:50.777
You look like the kind of a man

11:50.877 --> 11:54.656
who can recognize a great
opportunity when he sees one.

11:54.756 --> 11:58.118
Now, by investing in a
Darkside Tour franchise,

11:58.218 --> 12:01.371
you can turn death into dollars.

12:01.471 --> 12:07.853
I can personally almost guarantee
you a 45% annual return.

12:08.019 --> 12:10.964
How about you guarantee
you pay for that last round?

12:11.064 --> 12:15.426
Frank, I am entertaining a client.

12:15.526 --> 12:19.430
Sir, by being a partial franchisee,

12:19.530 --> 12:24.185
you can own 5% for a mere $600.

12:24.285 --> 12:27.584
What do you say? Do we have a deal?

12:30.541 --> 12:33.339
Your family will thank you.

12:33.670 --> 12:35.171
(CHUCKLES)

12:40.969 --> 12:43.037
- What is it?
- Bad luck.

12:43.137 --> 12:45.165
Come on.

12:45.265 --> 12:48.251
Frank, you are a witness
to this transaction.

12:48.351 --> 12:50.086
Morty, let's go, we got a full
hearse waiting, come on.

12:50.186 --> 12:51.713
Well, let them wait.

12:51.813 --> 12:54.591
May we have another
round, please, to welcome

12:54.691 --> 12:58.970
the newest member
of the Darkside family.

12:59.070 --> 13:01.931
Bridget, it is always
a delight to see you.

13:02.031 --> 13:03.975
You know,

13:04.075 --> 13:07.478
you are never too young
to invest in your future.

13:07.578 --> 13:10.064
Morty, you've already given
me a dozen brochures.

13:10.164 --> 13:11.941
I'll let you know when my
father reads them, okay?

13:12.041 --> 13:14.194
She's a great kid, Cody.

13:14.294 --> 13:17.468
May I have another drink, sir?

13:24.387 --> 13:25.997
What the hell is that?

13:26.097 --> 13:27.665
Red special rye.

13:27.765 --> 13:30.168
Cola and water. You've had enough.

13:30.268 --> 13:33.463
How dare you!

13:33.563 --> 13:36.441
I am as dry as can be.

13:39.902 --> 13:42.700
Cody? The usual?

13:44.032 --> 13:45.225
Thank you.

13:45.325 --> 13:47.042
This'll just take a second.

13:52.081 --> 13:53.733
I'm sober.

13:53.833 --> 13:56.006
I'm sober!

13:56.753 --> 13:59.096
Wait. Wait.

14:02.425 --> 14:05.078
Okay. Give me your comb.

14:05.178 --> 14:08.164
I don't have one.
You look fine, come on.

14:08.264 --> 14:10.166
It's a great day today, Cody.

14:10.266 --> 14:14.545
I just sold another 5%
share in the franchise.

14:14.645 --> 14:17.465
Look, Morty, we got a full
hearse waiting for the tour,

14:17.565 --> 14:19.717
I even suckered two rubes
for the deluxe package.

14:19.817 --> 14:21.886
- Let's go.
- Just two?

14:21.986 --> 14:23.388
You're slipping, kid.

14:23.488 --> 14:26.182
I was in kind of a hurry. Bridget and I
have a date to meet up with some kids

14:26.282 --> 14:28.017
from school down at the go-kart park.

14:28.117 --> 14:30.085
Ah, l'amour!

14:30.203 --> 14:33.022
But one day you'll wake up.

14:33.122 --> 14:37.110
And you'll realize there is only
one thing a woman wants.

14:37.210 --> 14:40.905
She will grab your heart,
tear it outta your chest,

14:41.005 --> 14:43.324
and throw it on the floor.

14:43.424 --> 14:45.576
Not now, Morty, please,
they're waiting.

14:45.676 --> 14:47.495
Indeed they are.

14:47.595 --> 14:52.976
Now, where are my keys?
The dark side awaits us.

14:56.020 --> 14:57.880
Where'd they put the door?

14:57.980 --> 14:59.549
You can't give the tour.

14:59.649 --> 15:02.051
- Why not?
- Well, because you're plastered.

15:02.151 --> 15:04.262
So, what difference does that make?

15:04.362 --> 15:06.389
What is rule number one?

15:06.489 --> 15:08.725
I know, I know, never turn
away a paying customer.

15:08.825 --> 15:12.770
I may be a little loose,
but I am not so far gone

15:12.870 --> 15:17.841
that I will turn away
a packed hearse.

15:18.167 --> 15:21.237
On the other hand, there's
always rule number two.

15:21.337 --> 15:22.280
Which is?

15:22.380 --> 15:25.349
Never kill a paying customer.

15:25.967 --> 15:28.244
We may have to cancel the tour.

15:28.344 --> 15:32.248
Here, give them their money back.

15:32.348 --> 15:36.478
Morty, you really are plastered,
there's almost $300 here.

15:36.644 --> 15:37.712
(KNOCKING AT DOOR)

15:37.812 --> 15:41.612
BRIDGET: Cody, let's go!
We're already a half an hour late.

15:44.193 --> 15:47.367
- Give me the keys.
- Where you going?

15:47.738 --> 15:51.309
Rule number three. There's no
such thing as a refund, remember?

15:51.409 --> 15:53.478
I'll give the stupid tour.

15:53.578 --> 15:56.706
That's my boy.

15:56.914 --> 15:58.107
Bridget.

15:58.207 --> 15:59.442
You ready to go?

15:59.542 --> 16:01.840
Ah, yeah.

16:03.671 --> 16:06.139
BRIDGET: (LAUGHS) What is it?

16:06.299 --> 16:09.202
Well, we don't have to take
the bus to the go-kart park.

16:09.302 --> 16:11.954
Marty's gonna give us
a ride in the hearse.

16:12.054 --> 16:13.771
Sort of.

16:15.391 --> 16:17.001
<i>CODY (ON MICROPHONE):
Welcome, death seekers.</i>

16:17.101 --> 16:19.837
<i>I am Baron Von Cody-stein,</i>

16:19.937 --> 16:23.549
<i>your substitute usher
into the Darkside.</i>

16:23.649 --> 16:28.620
<i>Our cruising altitude this afternoon
will be six feet under.</i> (LAUGHS EVILLY)

16:32.408 --> 16:36.562
<i>If there's anything we can do to
make your tour more terrifying,</i>

16:36.662 --> 16:40.086
<i>please do not hesitate to scream.</i>

16:40.917 --> 16:42.418
(WOMAN SCREAMING)

16:43.461 --> 16:46.055
Is there gonna be a bathroom stop?

16:46.631 --> 16:48.849
When are we gonna
see the death houses?

16:56.265 --> 16:59.735
There's some carols in the glove box.
Give me number fifteen?

17:06.983 --> 17:10.762
From this cliff high
above the Pacific Ocean,

17:10.863 --> 17:13.582
lies the death site of...

17:15.910 --> 17:17.686
You gave me the wrong card.

17:17.787 --> 17:20.585
Oh, did I?

17:21.332 --> 17:23.378
Here you go.

17:26.712 --> 17:28.698
WOMAN:
My husband is sick but he ain't dead!

17:28.798 --> 17:31.868
Get that creepy-ass vehicle
off of my property!

17:31.968 --> 17:33.845
There ain't nobody dead.

17:34.136 --> 17:36.998
And stay outta this neighborhood,
don't you come back in this neighborhood

17:37.098 --> 17:39.083
no more, we don't need
'em like you in here!

17:39.183 --> 17:43.129
We are a happy family here, we don't
need you in this neighborhood!

17:43.229 --> 17:46.716
<i>Uh... By the way, that was
the final resting home</i>

17:46.816 --> 17:49.135
<i>of Bela Lugosi.</i>

17:49.235 --> 17:51.863
Well, then, who the hell was that?

17:52.321 --> 17:54.348
<i>His stepdaughter, Stella Lugosi.</i>

17:54.448 --> 17:55.949
Aw!

18:00.329 --> 18:02.456
I should've taken the bus.

18:02.665 --> 18:05.568
Look, this is the last stop and
then we're there, okay? I promise.

18:05.668 --> 18:08.738
You'll love this one,
this is my favorite.

18:08.838 --> 18:10.990
<i>These ruins you see on the right</i>

18:11.090 --> 18:15.286
<i>are all that remains of Harry
Houdini's once vast mansion.</i>

18:15.386 --> 18:19.290
<i>Listen carefully and you
can hear his screams.</i>

18:19.390 --> 18:22.585
<i>During his life, he could
escape from any bonds,</i>

18:22.685 --> 18:27.089
<i>yet his spirit cannot escape
from these haunted grounds.</i>

18:27.189 --> 18:28.690
(WOMAN SCREAMS)

18:32.945 --> 18:34.446
(MAN CHUCKLES)

18:56.302 --> 18:57.803
(COUGHING)

19:41.263 --> 19:42.764
(GROANS)

19:57.154 --> 19:58.655
(GRUNTS)

20:21.178 --> 20:22.788
(LEPRECHAUN GROANS)

20:22.888 --> 20:24.685
Ah. Ha-ha!

20:28.936 --> 20:30.421
Bah!

20:30.521 --> 20:32.364
Blended Canadian?

20:33.315 --> 20:36.364
The only whiskey is
Irish whiskey. Ugh!

20:38.863 --> 20:40.364
Ha!

20:40.531 --> 20:43.409
Is that a bit of gold I see?

20:46.662 --> 20:48.163
(MAN GROANS)

20:54.420 --> 20:56.467
(MAN STRUGGLING)

20:57.214 --> 21:00.910
Sit back, my friend.
You may feel some pain.

21:01.010 --> 21:03.854
'Tis a pity I forgot my novocaine.
(LAUGHS)

21:04.346 --> 21:05.847
(GRUNTS)

21:07.558 --> 21:09.059
(CRACKING)

21:15.608 --> 21:17.109
(GRUNTS)

21:27.953 --> 21:29.545
Ah. Ha-ha!

21:34.293 --> 21:36.386
Now, rinse.

21:37.463 --> 21:38.964
(MAN GROANS)

21:39.381 --> 21:40.882
(LAUGHING)

21:47.515 --> 21:49.016
(GROANING)

21:59.401 --> 22:00.902
(LEPRECHAUN CHUCKLING)

22:03.948 --> 22:05.449
(KARTS PASSING)

22:09.245 --> 22:10.746
(TIRES SCREECHING)

22:16.085 --> 22:18.337
What the hell are we doing here?

22:18.796 --> 22:21.323
Uh, bathroom stop, ten minutes.

22:21.423 --> 22:23.425
Thank God!

22:24.093 --> 22:25.765
CODY: Bridget, wait a second.

22:30.641 --> 22:32.084
Ian.

22:32.184 --> 22:34.754
Bridget, I'm glad you could make it.

22:34.854 --> 22:36.005
Where is everybody?

22:36.105 --> 22:37.423
They're already down at the track.

22:37.523 --> 22:40.468
Did you change your hairstyle?
It looks great.

22:40.568 --> 22:42.011
(LAUGHS) Thanks.

22:42.111 --> 22:43.954
Bridget.

22:47.491 --> 22:49.685
Can we just go outside
and talk for a second?

22:49.785 --> 22:51.286
IAN: Cody.

22:51.787 --> 22:54.415
- Still running that classy tour, huh?
- (DEEP BREATHING)

22:55.457 --> 22:58.110
Come on, Bridget,
let's get down to the track.

22:58.210 --> 23:00.446
I saved a special crash
helmet just for you.

23:00.546 --> 23:01.697
Don't you have to work?

23:01.797 --> 23:05.050
Not if you're here. I can get
someone to cover for me.

23:11.473 --> 23:12.875
(HEAVY BREATHING)

23:12.975 --> 23:15.336
Hey, Billy. I gotta
take the night off.

23:15.436 --> 23:17.087
Can you come down and watch the shop?

23:17.187 --> 23:19.485
Listen, Bridget, I'm really sorry...

23:20.316 --> 23:22.534
- Oh, my God!
- (BARKING)

23:23.319 --> 23:25.162
Andretti! No!

23:25.863 --> 23:29.162
These are our friends. Now scram.

23:31.827 --> 23:34.204
That's just Andretti, our guard dog.

23:34.496 --> 23:37.169
- Come on, let's go start our engines.
- (BRIDGET LAUGHS)

23:39.752 --> 23:41.595
Bridget.

23:41.795 --> 23:44.172
Just give us a second, okay?

23:46.008 --> 23:47.493
What if I come by
and pick you up later?

23:47.593 --> 23:50.437
It's okay, I'm sure one of the
guys can give me a ride home.

23:50.763 --> 23:52.856
Wait a second.

23:53.182 --> 23:55.730
Look, next time things
will be different.

23:56.018 --> 23:58.646
What makes you think there's
gonna be a next time?

24:01.523 --> 24:03.821
MAN: Where we going now?

24:04.026 --> 24:08.451
This is our moment of silence for the souls
of the damned we visited on the tour.

24:09.114 --> 24:10.808
You know, this tour sucks.

24:10.908 --> 24:12.518
I told you this was a rip-off.

24:12.618 --> 24:15.771
Yeah, he's right. Why don't you just
take us back to Broadway, okay?

24:15.871 --> 24:17.314
Fine!

24:17.414 --> 24:18.915
(ALL EXCLAIM)

24:21.585 --> 24:23.428
(SIRENS BLARING)

24:25.923 --> 24:29.368
Operating a vehicle-for-hire
with only a learner's permit,

24:29.468 --> 24:30.536
running a red light,

24:30.636 --> 24:32.621
endangering the lives of passengers,

24:32.721 --> 24:37.567
no insurance, and six
seatbeit violations.

24:37.851 --> 24:40.129
These are serious offenses.

24:40.229 --> 24:41.380
That punk.

24:41.480 --> 24:44.133
When I get him home,
I'm gonna throttle him.

24:44.233 --> 24:47.553
Just take it easy. I think we
gave him a pretty good scare.

24:47.653 --> 24:51.140
Well, you just show me where to sign,
I'll take him off your shoulders.

24:51.240 --> 24:54.268
I can only release
him to his parents.

24:54.368 --> 24:56.687
Oh, his parents passed
away three years ago.

24:56.787 --> 24:58.731
God rest their souls.

24:58.831 --> 25:01.254
I'm his legal guardian.

25:05.045 --> 25:07.047
Um, do you have a pen?

25:15.431 --> 25:17.433
The kid with the hearse.

25:17.891 --> 25:19.376
Sergeant...

25:19.476 --> 25:21.712
You look like you're about to retire.

25:21.812 --> 25:25.441
Have you ever thought about
investing in a franchise?

25:26.567 --> 25:27.676
My pen?

25:27.776 --> 25:30.278
Oh, right.

25:31.030 --> 25:33.057
Well, you just keep this
and think it through.

25:33.157 --> 25:35.785
Have a good night, Sergeant.

25:39.288 --> 25:40.481
What did you think?

25:40.581 --> 25:42.358
Did you think these guys
wouldn't catch you?

25:42.458 --> 25:44.026
These are LA's finest.

25:44.126 --> 25:45.527
Yeah, I guess I just wasn't thinking.

25:45.627 --> 25:46.987
Damn straight!

25:47.087 --> 25:49.430
Thank you, officer.

25:49.673 --> 25:52.517
Why don't you take one
of these for yourself?

25:56.138 --> 25:57.748
You missed your calling,
you should've been an actor.

25:57.848 --> 25:58.832
There's no money in it.

25:58.932 --> 26:00.000
How you feeling?

26:00.100 --> 26:03.649
My stomach, you know.
Nothing a little Bromo won't cure.

26:03.896 --> 26:04.880
(MAN SHOUTING)

26:04.980 --> 26:08.759
No, I'm telling you, this guy came
out of a tree up at Houdini's place.

26:08.859 --> 26:12.363
And he tore my gold tooth out, look.

26:12.529 --> 26:13.722
Can you give a description?

26:13.822 --> 26:16.934
Yeah, yeah. He was
about three feet tall,

26:17.034 --> 26:20.396
had a green suit, and striped socks,
and a little hat, and a little hat.

26:20.496 --> 26:23.732
And I bet he had little gold
buckles on his little black shoes.

26:23.832 --> 26:26.193
Yeah! Yeah, that's right! Yes, yes!

26:26.293 --> 26:28.529
Happy St-Patrick's Day, boys.

26:28.629 --> 26:30.072
Get him out of here.

26:30.172 --> 26:32.574
No, no, no!

26:32.674 --> 26:35.327
Come on, look at me, he hurt me,
he's gonna hurt somebody else.

26:35.427 --> 26:38.330
Let me go! Let me go! Listen!

26:38.430 --> 26:41.417
You see that? You keep drinking,
you're gonna see little green men.

26:41.517 --> 26:43.127
Don't be a wise-ass.

26:43.227 --> 26:46.714
This place gives me the creeps,
let's get out of here.

26:46.814 --> 26:48.841
There's gonna be blood on your
hands if you don't do something!

26:48.941 --> 26:51.301
He's gonna jump
somebody else! Let me go!

26:51.401 --> 26:54.700
Let me go! He's gonna
hurt somebody! He hurt me!

26:59.326 --> 27:04.377
Spin, spin, my little guide, point
the way to my fresh young bride.

27:12.256 --> 27:14.283
What is this?

27:14.383 --> 27:15.993
It's a quarter.

27:16.093 --> 27:17.594
What'd you expect?

27:19.096 --> 27:21.457
Your gold would be nice.

27:21.557 --> 27:23.183
Funny.

27:23.433 --> 27:25.544
Tim Streeter, United Creative Agency.

27:25.644 --> 27:27.646
Call me if you get a showcase.

27:28.564 --> 27:30.065
Ah.

27:32.734 --> 27:34.136
(SCREAMS)

27:34.236 --> 27:36.079
Oh. (LAUGHS)

27:39.408 --> 27:41.751
Methinks I'm going to like this town.

27:44.329 --> 27:46.331
Finger-licking good. (LAUGHS)

27:48.083 --> 27:50.051
(MUSIC PLAYING)

28:13.525 --> 28:15.026
<i>MAN: (ON TV) Kiss me.</i>

28:34.504 --> 28:36.256
Bridget?

28:40.761 --> 28:42.638
(KNOCKING ON DOOR)

28:43.555 --> 28:45.602
- What are you doing?
- Shh!

28:48.769 --> 28:51.213
Thirty-one minutes! It's free!

28:51.313 --> 28:54.591
Nothing tastes as
good as a free pizza.

28:54.691 --> 28:58.695
Now if I could only figure
out how to get free beer.

28:58.820 --> 29:00.347
Everything's a scam to you, isn't it?

29:00.447 --> 29:03.791
Damn right. Come here.

29:03.992 --> 29:05.644
Have some pizza.

29:05.744 --> 29:07.729
No, I ain't hungry.

29:07.829 --> 29:09.501
What's a matter?

29:09.706 --> 29:12.234
I think I really blew
it with Bridget today.

29:12.334 --> 29:16.238
She's a great girl,
how could you do such a thing?

29:16.338 --> 29:19.449
Well, you got drunk,
so I decided to break our date

29:19.549 --> 29:21.869
and give the stupid tour.

29:21.969 --> 29:23.370
You did the right thing.

29:23.470 --> 29:25.330
You went after the cash.

29:25.430 --> 29:28.041
Women are trouble every time.

29:28.141 --> 29:31.360
Forget her. Come on.

29:32.479 --> 29:34.423
We'll play some cards.

29:34.523 --> 29:37.801
Keep your eye on the red card.

29:37.901 --> 29:39.261
Three Card Monte.

29:39.361 --> 29:43.365
Oh. It's a perfect game.

29:43.573 --> 29:47.227
The chump gets lured in,
he forgets everything else.

29:47.327 --> 29:51.565
All he sees is that
money in front of him.

29:51.665 --> 29:53.942
And then he gets
that look in his eye,

29:54.042 --> 29:57.070
and you know he's a dead man.

29:57.170 --> 29:59.889
And then it's time.
And you make your move.

30:03.343 --> 30:05.454
Where you going?

30:05.554 --> 30:08.557
I've been a chump,
it's time to make my move.

30:12.561 --> 30:13.879
<i>IAN:
So did you have a good time tonight?</i>

30:13.979 --> 30:16.777
Yeah. Thanks for the ride.

30:19.109 --> 30:21.136
Hey, wait up.

30:21.236 --> 30:23.096
You said your parents weren't home.

30:23.196 --> 30:24.473
So?

30:24.573 --> 30:26.808
Well, aren't you gonna invite me in?

30:26.908 --> 30:29.186
Ian, you know I'm
going out with Cody.

30:29.286 --> 30:30.812
I thought you guys called it quits.

30:30.912 --> 30:32.522
No, we didn't. Good night, Ian.

30:32.622 --> 30:33.899
Just a second.

30:33.999 --> 30:36.443
I took the whole night off for you.

30:36.543 --> 30:38.904
And what about those chili dogs?

30:39.004 --> 30:40.989
Ian, you better go.

30:41.089 --> 30:43.742
Come on. Just a couple of minutes.

30:43.842 --> 30:45.559
I said, "No."

30:46.428 --> 30:48.497
I get it. You're just a tease.

30:48.597 --> 30:51.566
- Well, tease this.
- (IAN GRUNTS)

30:54.311 --> 30:56.108
Stuck-up bitch.

30:59.524 --> 31:01.446
BRIDGET: Ian?

31:03.695 --> 31:06.348
- Bridget.
- Ian?

31:06.448 --> 31:10.578
I'm so sorry. I don't
know what I was thinking.

31:12.079 --> 31:14.064
What are you thinking now?

31:14.164 --> 31:18.464
I was thinking maybe I
could make it up to you?

31:19.378 --> 31:21.405
That's a start.

31:21.505 --> 31:25.009
Well, are you just gonna stand there?

31:37.479 --> 31:38.980
(LAUGHS)

31:40.148 --> 31:41.466
You hear that?

31:41.566 --> 31:44.740
Ian, come on.

31:46.029 --> 31:49.328
Why don't we go inside?
This place is giving me the creeps.

31:49.491 --> 31:52.164
I may change my mind again.

32:12.180 --> 32:14.057
Kiss me.

32:15.517 --> 32:19.362
A vision before you.
Appears to be true.

32:21.273 --> 32:25.869
But a leprechaun's magic
fools humans like you.

32:29.197 --> 32:30.698
(LAUGHS)

32:42.794 --> 32:44.295
(IAN SCREAMS)

32:48.967 --> 32:51.411
(IN BRIDGET'S VOICE) Was it as
good for you as it was for me?

32:51.511 --> 32:52.496
(LEPRECHAUN VOICE) Ha!

32:52.596 --> 32:54.706
You shouldn't fool with me, lass.

32:54.806 --> 32:56.307
(LAUGHS)

32:56.433 --> 32:59.378
She sneezes once, she sneezes twice,

32:59.478 --> 33:02.047
she'll be my bride when
she sneezes thrice.

33:02.147 --> 33:03.648
(LAUGHING)

33:08.820 --> 33:09.971
(DOORBELL RINGS)

33:10.071 --> 33:14.576
(CHUCKLES) Ian, you idiot.
You just never give up.

33:17.037 --> 33:18.897
Forget it.

33:18.997 --> 33:20.498
(DOORBELL RINGS)

33:25.128 --> 33:27.531
Get out of here or I'm
going to call the police.

33:27.631 --> 33:29.132
(DOORBELL RINGS)

33:33.428 --> 33:35.851
You really are mad at me.

33:36.515 --> 33:38.062
Trick or treat.

33:38.266 --> 33:39.668
Wrong holiday.

33:39.768 --> 33:42.487
Got it covered. Can I come in?

33:46.942 --> 33:48.989
This is a surprise.

33:53.073 --> 33:55.291
I was a real jerk today.

33:55.617 --> 33:57.585
Here. Take 'em.

33:59.371 --> 34:01.064
They're beautiful.

34:01.164 --> 34:03.024
Not as beautiful as you.

34:03.124 --> 34:05.297
- Do you forgive me?
- (LAUGHS)

34:05.460 --> 34:07.837
- Cody.
- Yep.

34:07.963 --> 34:10.364
I can never stay mad at you.

34:10.465 --> 34:11.574
I've learned my lesson.

34:11.675 --> 34:15.145
From now on I promise nothing's
gonna come between us.

34:17.556 --> 34:19.148
(WINDOW SLIDING)

34:22.143 --> 34:24.145
Let's go put these in some water.

34:25.897 --> 34:27.132
(BLOWS)

34:27.232 --> 34:28.733
(SNEEZES)

34:28.984 --> 34:31.469
Great. I buy you flowers
and you're allergic to them.

34:31.570 --> 34:33.743
I'm not allergic. Come on.

34:36.074 --> 34:38.601
"Cody." Man of few words.

34:38.702 --> 34:40.270
I didn't know if you'd be home.

34:40.370 --> 34:42.731
Didn't want you to think some
stalker was leaving you flowers.

34:42.831 --> 34:44.331
(SNEEZES)

34:44.456 --> 34:47.485
Gesundheit. Maybe you should put
those in another room or something.

34:47.585 --> 34:48.695
It's not the flowers.

34:48.795 --> 34:52.139
But even if it was, it doesn't
matter because I love them.

34:52.591 --> 34:53.783
(BLOWS)

34:53.882 --> 34:55.243
(SNEEZES)

34:55.342 --> 34:56.844
God ble... Ahhh!

35:03.852 --> 35:05.353
(LAUGHING)

35:05.645 --> 35:07.146
(SCREAMS)

35:07.480 --> 35:10.550
I've searched this fair
land far and wide.

35:10.650 --> 35:14.120
At last I've got me
a leprechaun bride.

35:14.904 --> 35:17.532
Who are you? How'd you get in here?

35:17.782 --> 35:19.283
(RATTLING)

35:22.162 --> 35:23.914
Cody!

35:25.040 --> 35:27.292
Somebody help!

35:29.294 --> 35:31.613
Somebody help!

35:31.713 --> 35:33.198
(BRIDGET SCREAMS)

35:33.298 --> 35:34.799
(LAUGHS)

35:36.217 --> 35:37.994
Please. What do you want?

35:38.094 --> 35:42.690
It's not a proper wedding without
a wedding ring, now, is it?

35:56.988 --> 36:00.392
With this ring I thee wed.

36:00.492 --> 36:01.476
(GASPS)

36:01.576 --> 36:04.249
I may now kiss the bride.

36:04.412 --> 36:05.913
(STRUGGLING)

36:11.461 --> 36:12.962
(CHOKING)

36:21.179 --> 36:23.602
That's a good girl.

36:24.933 --> 36:27.185
Ah! My gold!

36:40.949 --> 36:43.602
- Are you okay?
- Yeah. I'm fine.

36:43.702 --> 36:46.330
Let's get the hell out of here.

36:47.372 --> 36:49.733
- He killed Ian.
- This is crazy.

36:49.833 --> 36:50.817
Ahhh!

36:50.917 --> 36:52.464
(BRIDGET SCREAMS)

36:53.461 --> 36:54.962
(WHIMPERING)

36:58.425 --> 37:00.222
(LEPRECHAUN SCREAMS)

37:05.306 --> 37:09.419
1,000 years ago a man stopped
me from taking my bride,

37:09.519 --> 37:11.504
I'll not let it happen again.

37:11.604 --> 37:14.232
Cody, please!

37:14.691 --> 37:16.659
Bridget!

37:17.485 --> 37:19.721
<i>Bridget!</i>

37:19.821 --> 37:21.848
LEPRECHAUN:
It ain't much, but it's home.

37:21.948 --> 37:23.449
(GASPING)

37:29.205 --> 37:31.673
What do you think of
your bridal chamber?

37:33.293 --> 37:35.261
It's awful.

37:35.378 --> 37:38.677
I know it lacks a woman's touch,
but you'll change that.

37:39.215 --> 37:41.513
Well, shall we?

37:43.011 --> 37:44.537
Oh, God, please.

37:44.637 --> 37:49.042
Aw. Now, now, my dear, I've waited
1,000 years for this night.

37:49.142 --> 37:50.418
But it was worth it.

37:50.518 --> 37:53.441
Just to claim an O'Day for my bride.

37:53.605 --> 37:56.949
Oh, my name's not O'Day.
You made a mistake.

37:57.192 --> 37:59.344
O'Day is in your blood.

37:59.444 --> 38:00.804
(SNIFFS)

38:00.904 --> 38:02.701
I can smell it.

38:03.865 --> 38:06.935
I know what you need.
A little Irish whiskey.

38:07.035 --> 38:09.003
Just to put you in the mood.

38:10.371 --> 38:12.544
Okay.

38:40.944 --> 38:43.242
That's the stuff.

38:46.324 --> 38:47.825
(PANTING)

38:56.334 --> 38:57.835
(SCREAMING)

38:58.837 --> 39:00.338
Ah!

39:00.713 --> 39:03.032
A little family reunion.

39:03.132 --> 39:06.119
You have his cheekbones. (LAUGHS)

39:06.219 --> 39:09.372
- No!
- I'm glad I have a frisky lass.

39:09.472 --> 39:12.270
I like to play games too.

39:12.392 --> 39:14.127
No. Please.

39:14.227 --> 39:16.171
Let's play...

39:16.271 --> 39:18.773
Bedtime for Bridget.

39:19.524 --> 39:21.025
(GASPS)

39:25.405 --> 39:27.849
(SCREAMS) How did we get here?

39:27.949 --> 39:31.999
A leprechaun's home
has many surprises.

39:32.203 --> 39:35.172
That's no way to treat the
father of your children.

39:36.332 --> 39:38.193
- Oh. Didn't I mention?
- No!

39:38.293 --> 39:40.862
You'll be bearing my wee ones soon.

39:40.962 --> 39:43.840
- Get me out of this!
- Oh, silence.

39:45.341 --> 39:46.967
(BRIDGET TREMBLES)

39:52.807 --> 39:54.083
(INHALES SHARPLY)

39:54.183 --> 39:57.983
LEPRECHAUN: I'm going to have
to make a few alterations.

39:58.271 --> 40:02.025
But afterward you should
be able to bear a full litter.

40:04.944 --> 40:07.222
These will need sharpening.

40:07.322 --> 40:08.932
Why?

40:09.032 --> 40:11.017
Why are you doing this?

40:11.117 --> 40:12.101
Aw.

40:12.201 --> 40:14.103
Don't worry your
little head about it.

40:14.203 --> 40:16.523
- You'll get used to the pain.
- (WHIMPERING)

40:16.623 --> 40:19.626
We'll have to make some
changes to your face as well.

40:19.792 --> 40:21.069
'Tis a fair face.

40:21.169 --> 40:23.905
But the wee ones won't suckle
if you don't look like them.

40:24.005 --> 40:28.180
- No!
- They can be very demanding at times.

40:30.511 --> 40:32.580
Many changes.

40:32.680 --> 40:34.707
Many changes.

40:34.807 --> 40:37.025
No!

40:37.143 --> 40:39.816
- No!
- Ah, stop that.

40:41.689 --> 40:43.691
I just want to go home.

40:44.359 --> 40:46.953
But you are home, my sweet.

40:47.111 --> 40:49.830
And home is where you'll stay.

40:53.284 --> 40:56.754
Something new, something old.

40:56.913 --> 41:01.509
Let's be together on
leprechaun's gold.

41:21.437 --> 41:23.339
It's missing.

41:23.439 --> 41:26.442
A gold shilling. It's not here.

41:27.735 --> 41:31.364
It's missing. I must have it back.

41:31.906 --> 41:33.999
(BRIDGET WHIMPERING)

41:42.583 --> 41:46.678
Don't leave me tied here, please.
I'll do anything.

41:46.879 --> 41:48.676
I'll do...

41:49.298 --> 41:52.927
I wanna make myself look
pretty for our wedding night.

41:53.594 --> 41:55.767
I wanna look pretty for you.

41:56.597 --> 42:00.101
You're my husband now.
I want to please you.

42:02.061 --> 42:03.904
That you will.

42:10.278 --> 42:12.655
Here's a proper wedding dress.

42:13.156 --> 42:15.875
Be sure you're wearing
it when I return.

42:20.997 --> 42:23.316
But before I go...

42:23.416 --> 42:25.526
Kiss me, I'm Irish.

42:25.626 --> 42:27.127
(SCREAMS)

42:30.631 --> 42:33.725
That's just a taste
of things to come.

42:34.135 --> 42:36.137
Rm going to get my gold.

42:37.055 --> 42:40.375
You'll try to escape,
but it's hopeless.

42:40.475 --> 42:41.976
(LAUGHS)

42:57.158 --> 42:59.581
Cody?

43:05.625 --> 43:08.569
I've searched this house
for my gold shilling.

43:08.669 --> 43:12.423
The fool that holds
it is due for a killing.

43:12.715 --> 43:14.558
WOMAN: Hey, Bill.

43:15.176 --> 43:16.744
I think we have a suspect.

43:16.844 --> 43:19.080
Found these flowers and
this note in the kitchen.

43:19.180 --> 43:20.581
Cody Engels.

43:20.681 --> 43:23.710
Parents told me he's the girl's boyfriend.
They said he's bad news.

43:23.810 --> 43:27.814
Anyway they had some fight this afternoon
and he brought over the roses.

43:50.044 --> 43:51.761
(SCREAMS IN FRUSTRATION)

44:17.488 --> 44:20.286
I don't know about that.

44:29.375 --> 44:31.252
No, I haven't seen him.

44:37.175 --> 44:39.202
- Morty?
- Jesus, kid.

44:39.302 --> 44:41.245
- How did you get in here?
- Fire escape.

44:41.345 --> 44:42.580
- Are you all right?
- Yeah. I'm fine.

44:42.680 --> 44:43.873
- You're not gonna believe this.
- Listen.

44:43.973 --> 44:46.417
The cops are looking
for you every place.

44:46.517 --> 44:50.797
They found this dead kid at Bridget's,
she's gone, everybody says you did it.

44:50.897 --> 44:52.006
Me? That's crazy! I would never...

44:52.106 --> 44:55.450
That's what I told the cops,
now what the hell happened?

44:55.610 --> 44:57.908
A leprechaun did it.

44:58.571 --> 44:59.806
- Maybe I should call the cops.
- No.

44:59.906 --> 45:02.283
Wait a second. Look at this.

45:06.287 --> 45:10.358
Okay. So you got a gold coin and it's old
and it looks like the one in this book.

45:10.458 --> 45:14.278
It's probably worth some cash.
But this leprechaun story...

45:14.378 --> 45:16.197
Give me that thing.

45:16.297 --> 45:17.615
Cody?

45:17.715 --> 45:20.368
If you were taking some dope,
you would tell me, right?

45:20.468 --> 45:23.913
Morty, you gotta believe me.
I saw a real leprechaun.

45:24.013 --> 45:27.834
You mean, like, three wishes,
and give me all your gold and like that?

45:27.934 --> 45:30.211
Get out of here, kid.
That's a fairy tale.

45:30.311 --> 45:33.172
This is no fairy tale.
I saw what it can do.

45:33.272 --> 45:36.050
Look. Leprechauns
are devious creatures.

45:36.150 --> 45:40.304
They are conniving. It says here they live
by trickery, even get pleasure out of it.

45:40.404 --> 45:43.808
Maybe I should've kept you away
from all this supernatural stuff.

45:43.908 --> 45:46.394
He dropped a rack of
pots on my head, Morty.

45:46.494 --> 45:48.104
Oh. Now I'm convinced.

45:48.204 --> 45:49.230
Look, look, look.

45:49.330 --> 45:52.900
They possess telekinetic powers
and can turn invisible at will.

45:53.000 --> 45:54.610
They are masters of illusion.

45:54.710 --> 45:58.239
Both leprechauns and fairies can
only be harmed by wrought iron.

45:58.339 --> 45:59.574
Right. Right.

45:59.674 --> 46:01.826
And they're all greedy as hell,

46:01.926 --> 46:05.288
and they love to drink,
and they make those shoes,

46:05.388 --> 46:08.416
and they all have little pots
of gold, and if you catch them,

46:08.516 --> 46:10.918
they grant you three wishes,
and all the rest of that crap.

46:11.018 --> 46:14.630
Look I have read that stuff.
It's made up.

46:14.730 --> 46:16.382
It's not real.

46:16.482 --> 46:19.468
I use that kind of junk to
sucker in the tourists.

46:19.568 --> 46:21.762
Would you listen to me please, Morty.

46:21.862 --> 46:24.974
On his thousandth birthday,
the leprechaun laid claim to the lass

46:25.074 --> 46:28.373
and by daybreak she was
never heard from again.

46:29.328 --> 46:31.705
My God. That's why
he came for Bridget.

46:32.498 --> 46:36.319
I should've returned this book
to the library five years ago.

46:36.419 --> 46:40.469
I don't know what you saw,
but leprechauns don't exist.

46:41.215 --> 46:45.936
What's that you say?
Leprechauns don't exist? Ha-ha!

46:47.096 --> 46:49.439
I want my gold.

46:51.517 --> 46:53.127
I'll not say it again.

46:53.227 --> 46:54.962
You know what I want.

46:55.062 --> 46:57.781
I'll trade you the coin for Bridget.

46:57.982 --> 47:04.489
Ah, a fair trade, lad. Give me the
coin, and she's yours, I promise.

47:11.746 --> 47:13.898
- Are you crazy?
- You can't trust a leprechaun.

47:13.998 --> 47:15.733
- Did you read the book?
- Let's get out of here.

47:15.833 --> 47:17.360
The place is crawling with cops.

47:17.460 --> 47:19.428
All right. Fire escape.

47:20.087 --> 47:21.930
(LEPRECHAUN GRUNTING)

47:23.883 --> 47:26.369
Hold on a second.
My foot's caught. Ahhh!

47:26.469 --> 47:29.848
Now you've done it.
You've welched on a leprechaun.

47:32.892 --> 47:34.393
(SCREAMS)

47:37.521 --> 47:39.966
That is one pissed off leprechaun.
Quick! To Brennan's!

47:40.066 --> 47:42.239
Great idea. It will be packed.

47:42.693 --> 47:43.678
(WOMAN LAUGHING)

47:43.778 --> 47:45.096
Did you see what happened
when he touched the bars?

47:45.196 --> 47:49.600
Yeah, yeah, yeah. Wrought iron.
Keep moving. Keep moving.

47:49.700 --> 47:51.201
(INDISTINCT CHATTERING)

48:06.884 --> 48:09.512
It's time to take a leak.

48:18.896 --> 48:21.319
- So how are we gonna get Bridget?
- (SHUSHING)

48:23.484 --> 48:25.952
Let me see that coin again.

48:29.031 --> 48:31.851
That son of a bitch is real.
I actually saw him.

48:31.951 --> 48:34.270
- Morty!
- Sorry. Force of habit.

48:34.370 --> 48:36.105
Every second we waste...

48:36.205 --> 48:37.440
Who knows what he's
doing to her right now.

48:37.540 --> 48:38.607
Don't worry about it, kid.

48:38.707 --> 48:43.053
I know how much she means to you.
We're gonna catch that little bastard.

48:44.046 --> 48:47.533
We're smarter. I know what I'm doing.

48:47.633 --> 48:48.909
Where are you going?

48:49.009 --> 48:50.931
I'm going to get a drink.

49:08.446 --> 49:10.243
(FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING)

49:20.499 --> 49:23.047
Yo, man! Want my gold?

49:24.879 --> 49:26.926
Come on.

49:29.717 --> 49:31.619
Take 'em.

49:31.719 --> 49:33.641
Thanks.

49:34.889 --> 49:36.936
It's real milk chocolate.

49:59.079 --> 50:01.957
- Watch it, nosebleed.
- Sorry, man.

50:19.433 --> 50:22.128
Morty, listen. Houdini's ruins.
Don't you remember?

50:22.228 --> 50:25.423
The drunk at the police station said
a leprechaun stole his gold tooth.

50:25.523 --> 50:28.634
He came out of a tree at Houdini's
ruins. That's where Bridget is.

50:28.734 --> 50:32.471
Let's go. Morty, come on.
Let's get out of here.

50:32.571 --> 50:36.016
Morty. Hello. Morty.
Come on, let's go.

50:36.116 --> 50:38.038
Morty?

50:38.327 --> 50:40.374
He's here.

50:46.460 --> 50:48.803
Maybe we should go now.

50:49.672 --> 50:52.140
Too late.

50:55.511 --> 50:58.038
Have I mentioned that I want my gold?

50:58.138 --> 50:59.373
Not until we get Bridget.

50:59.473 --> 51:03.711
Bridget? Don't you know
she's a married woman.

51:03.811 --> 51:07.565
Let me handle it. I got an idea.

51:08.983 --> 51:10.484
Um.

51:11.151 --> 51:13.846
Listen up, people. Listen up.

51:13.946 --> 51:17.224
My little buddy here
just got married.

51:17.324 --> 51:22.500
What do you say we raise our
glasses and toast his good health.

51:22.663 --> 51:26.588
- Cheers.
- Congratulations.

51:30.254 --> 51:32.756
Have a drink. It's on me.

51:35.009 --> 51:37.077
You got a problem?

51:37.177 --> 51:41.040
Maybe it's just part of
that leprechaun myth

51:41.140 --> 51:43.483
that they can all hold their liquor.

51:44.018 --> 51:46.754
Now don't be ashamed.
It's nothing to be embarrassed about.

51:46.854 --> 51:50.799
Why don't I just get you
a little green lemonade.

51:50.899 --> 51:52.400
(ALL LAUGHING)

52:02.286 --> 52:04.379
I can handle my drink.

52:04.747 --> 52:06.248
(ALL CHEERING)

52:09.043 --> 52:10.819
Oh, really?

52:10.919 --> 52:15.366
Frank, can I have a bottle
of that Red special rye.

52:15.466 --> 52:19.537
I'd like to share with my little
buddy here how a real man drinks.

52:19.637 --> 52:21.764
FRANK: Coming right up.

52:25.517 --> 52:26.877
Uh, what are you doing?

52:26.977 --> 52:29.525
Watch it and learn.

52:41.575 --> 52:43.076
(ALL CHEERING)

52:44.578 --> 52:47.147
Drink what you want,
drink what you're able,

52:47.247 --> 52:50.250
if you're drinkin' with me,
you'll be under the table.

52:50.584 --> 52:53.821
Come on. Let's cheer him on.
He's one of us.

52:53.921 --> 52:58.534
(CHANTING) One of us. One of us.
One of us. One of us. One of us.

52:58.634 --> 53:02.204
One of us. One of us.
One of us. One of us.

53:02.304 --> 53:05.749
One of us. One of us.
One of us. One of us.

53:05.849 --> 53:09.545
One of us. One of us. One of us.

53:09.645 --> 53:11.146
(ALL CHEERING)

53:19.863 --> 53:23.788
One way or another I'll find
a way out of this hell hole.

53:50.227 --> 53:51.728
(GRUNTS)

54:12.249 --> 54:16.470
You're my hero, homie. I'm 5,000.

54:20.841 --> 54:23.410
- When do we go get Bridget?
- Relax.

54:23.510 --> 54:26.080
She's safe as long as he's here.

54:26.180 --> 54:29.833
Pour all you want, pour all you can,

54:29.933 --> 54:33.687
you won't beat me
'cause I'm a leprechaun.

54:34.062 --> 54:35.839
Chaun. (LAUGHS)

54:35.939 --> 54:37.440
(BURPS)

54:40.569 --> 54:43.263
You thought you were fast.
You thought you were sporty.

54:43.363 --> 54:47.226
You thought you were clever,
but not as clever as Morty.

54:47.326 --> 54:49.373
All right. You're done.
Now let's go get Bridget.

55:12.392 --> 55:16.817
Didn't anybody ever tell you not
to drink and levitate? (LAUGHS)

55:17.064 --> 55:21.785
Face it, my little friend.
You're gonna have to do what we ask.

55:22.903 --> 55:25.030
(MUSIC PLAYING ON JUKEBOX)

55:26.532 --> 55:27.641
(GRUNTS)

55:27.741 --> 55:29.643
- You okay?
- I'm fine.

55:29.743 --> 55:33.122
Go get the little son of a bitch.

55:41.839 --> 55:43.699
No sign of him.

55:43.799 --> 55:45.993
I'm sorry I let you down, kid.
(SIGHS)

55:46.093 --> 55:49.016
I had my chance and I blew it.

55:50.430 --> 55:54.685
Look. Wrought iron is the one
thing that can harm him, right?

55:55.435 --> 55:57.437
I got an idea.

56:20.294 --> 56:23.513
Kiss this, you slimy creep.

56:58.165 --> 57:03.136
Yeah. I have a little wedding
present for you when you get home.

57:07.007 --> 57:09.009
(LEPRECHAUN GROANING)

57:15.390 --> 57:16.891
(SIGHS)

57:21.605 --> 57:25.905
Okay, pal. St. Patrick's
Day is over. Time to go home.

57:27.152 --> 57:30.872
Don't be giving me any attitude,
all right? I got to close up.

57:31.448 --> 57:33.245
Aye.

57:34.701 --> 57:38.000
Very good. We have a method actor.

57:39.706 --> 57:41.233
What's you next gig, huh?

57:41.333 --> 57:44.461
One of Santa's elves or one
of the seven dwarfs? (LAUGHS)

57:45.837 --> 57:48.448
I'm not an elf or a dwarf.

57:48.548 --> 57:50.284
I'm a leprechaun.

57:50.384 --> 57:52.452
Look, I don't care if you're
the Tooth Fairy, all right?

57:52.552 --> 57:55.430
I just want you to pay up
so I can get out of here.

57:55.931 --> 57:59.560
Ah. So it's my gold
you'll be wanting.

57:59.726 --> 58:04.464
Uh, Gold Card, Visa,
MasterCard, I'd prefer cash,

58:04.564 --> 58:05.757
but maybe you're a little short.

58:05.857 --> 58:07.358
(LAUGHS)

58:08.902 --> 58:11.029
Boom. Gotcha.

58:17.160 --> 58:20.397
One should never try to
take a leprechaun's gold.

58:20.497 --> 58:23.045
You're really into this, aren't you?

58:23.208 --> 58:26.069
(IMITATING LEPRECHAUN) "One should
never try to take a leprechaun's gold."

58:26.169 --> 58:27.670
(LAUGHS)

58:29.006 --> 58:30.723
You kill me.

58:32.050 --> 58:33.160
Huh?

58:33.260 --> 58:35.370
Now there's an idea.

58:35.470 --> 58:36.496
Ahhh!

58:36.596 --> 58:38.097
(LAUGHS)

58:38.765 --> 58:40.266
(SCREAMING)

58:45.605 --> 58:49.134
Please, no!

58:49.234 --> 58:50.735
(MAN SCREAMS)

58:58.452 --> 58:59.978
Don't touch. It's hot.

59:00.078 --> 59:01.625
(LAUGHS)

59:04.041 --> 59:07.215
Heigh-ho, heigh-ho.

59:08.086 --> 59:09.363
(DOG BARKS)

59:09.463 --> 59:12.491
Come on, Andretti. Come on.
Yeah. We're friends. Yes.

59:12.591 --> 59:15.869
There you go.
Little late night snack. Yum.

59:15.969 --> 59:17.537
Nice work.

59:17.637 --> 59:20.415
Now are you sure that
safe is big enough?

59:20.515 --> 59:23.377
Yeah. It's huge.
Big old wrought iron thing.

59:23.477 --> 59:25.754
If it's a tight fit,
I ain't shedding any tears.

59:25.854 --> 59:28.982
Me neither. Come on.

59:37.324 --> 59:39.622
There she is.

59:43.121 --> 59:45.107
These won't work.
How are we gonna open this?

59:45.207 --> 59:47.004
Combination.

59:47.334 --> 59:48.960
I've taught you well.

59:49.127 --> 59:52.722
Yeah? I'll send you a
postcard from San Quentin.

59:52.839 --> 59:54.324
Hey, give me a hand
with this stuff, will you?

59:54.424 --> 59:56.016
Okay.

59:59.805 --> 01:00:01.807
Put it back.

01:00:05.268 --> 01:00:07.111
Come on.

01:00:07.479 --> 01:00:08.980
(BOTH GRUNTING)

01:00:09.648 --> 01:00:14.428
We'll get a double hernia trying
to lift this into the hearse.

01:00:14.528 --> 01:00:17.806
Uh. Try to find something that
builds a ramp and I will get the car.

01:00:17.906 --> 01:00:19.874
Okay.

01:00:20.867 --> 01:00:22.368
Ramp.

01:00:22.702 --> 01:00:24.187
Security, buddy. Keep your
hands where I can see them.

01:00:24.287 --> 01:00:26.023
Damn! You're breaking my arm.

01:00:26.123 --> 01:00:28.150
You just tripped off a silent alarm,
buddy. You're going down.

01:00:28.250 --> 01:00:30.610
Going down where?
You're a freaking security guard.

01:00:30.710 --> 01:00:33.113
That's security officer, pal.

01:00:33.213 --> 01:00:34.364
Any more perps around?

01:00:34.464 --> 01:00:37.117
Perp? What the hell
are you talking about?

01:00:37.217 --> 01:00:38.889
You're mine, tough guy.

01:00:40.470 --> 01:00:42.313
Wait right here.

01:00:56.236 --> 01:00:57.737
(DOOR OPENS)

01:01:42.199 --> 01:01:43.700
(DOOR CLOSES)

01:01:48.121 --> 01:01:49.147
(SIGHS)

01:01:49.247 --> 01:01:51.441
You may think this
line is getting old.

01:01:51.541 --> 01:01:54.339
But believe me, son. I want my gold.

01:02:05.347 --> 01:02:06.848
(GRUNTING)

01:02:10.977 --> 01:02:14.339
Look, pal. There's a big
misunderstanding here.

01:02:14.439 --> 01:02:19.052
Now if you just un-cuff me, I can
reach my wallet. You get what I mean?

01:02:19.152 --> 01:02:21.513
Are you trying to bribe me, scumbag?

01:02:21.613 --> 01:02:25.663
I take my job seriously.
Don't try anything.

01:02:26.493 --> 01:02:29.646
I've got 60 hours of combat training.

01:02:29.746 --> 01:02:31.247
(GLASS SHATTERING)

01:02:32.791 --> 01:02:34.651
You should've had 65.

01:02:34.751 --> 01:02:37.504
This guy's got to have a gun.

01:02:38.380 --> 01:02:39.447
(MORTY GRUNTS)

01:02:39.547 --> 01:02:42.345
It's my old friend,
the drinking champ.

01:02:42.509 --> 01:02:45.787
You didn't happen to see the young
lad around here now, did you?

01:02:45.887 --> 01:02:47.205
No, I came here alone.

01:02:47.305 --> 01:02:49.398
Wrong answer.

01:02:57.274 --> 01:02:59.759
- Where is the boy?
- I don't know.

01:02:59.859 --> 01:03:02.077
I'm here, shortstuff.

01:03:02.862 --> 01:03:04.890
- Come and get it.
- LEPRECHAUN: Ah!

01:03:04.990 --> 01:03:06.766
My gold.

01:03:06.866 --> 01:03:08.768
The offer still stands.

01:03:08.868 --> 01:03:10.770
The coin for Bridget.

01:03:10.870 --> 01:03:12.397
Don't give it to him.

01:03:12.497 --> 01:03:16.484
I'll keep what I have.
And I'll let the two of you live.

01:03:16.584 --> 01:03:17.736
That's my offer.

01:03:17.836 --> 01:03:21.010
- No deal.
- MORTY: That's telling him, Cody!

01:03:21.589 --> 01:03:24.534
So be it. I'll come get it myself.

01:03:24.634 --> 01:03:26.135
(LAUGHING)

01:03:28.054 --> 01:03:29.555
(LEPRECHAUN SCREAMING)

01:03:35.061 --> 01:03:37.631
Nice job, Cody. I'm proud of you.

01:03:37.731 --> 01:03:38.840
Hey, you all right.

01:03:38.940 --> 01:03:43.661
Well, I used to think hangovers
were bad. I just hope nothing's broken.

01:03:44.904 --> 01:03:47.156
How does it feel in there, huh?

01:03:47.866 --> 01:03:49.976
Ahhh! Let me out of here.

01:03:50.076 --> 01:03:51.577
Ahhh!

01:03:53.371 --> 01:03:56.358
What's the matter, Houdini?
Can't get out?

01:03:56.458 --> 01:03:58.255
Let's go get Bridget.

01:03:58.877 --> 01:04:00.674
Absolutely.

01:04:01.254 --> 01:04:03.131
What is it?

01:04:03.465 --> 01:04:07.244
Well, we need a ramp
to get this into the car.

01:04:07.344 --> 01:04:08.870
You know what? There's some
two-by-fours in the closet.

01:04:08.970 --> 01:04:11.017
Well, get 'em.

01:04:20.982 --> 01:04:22.592
What the hell are you doing?

01:04:22.692 --> 01:04:25.194
Morty, you locked me in.

01:04:26.196 --> 01:04:28.932
It's payback time.

01:04:29.032 --> 01:04:30.684
LEPRECHAUN: Get me out of here.

01:04:30.784 --> 01:04:34.187
Not yet. Come on.
You know the routine.

01:04:34.287 --> 01:04:37.524
You're caught.
You owe me three wishes.

01:04:37.624 --> 01:04:39.901
Morty, we got to go get Bridget now.

01:04:40.001 --> 01:04:43.530
I know what I'm doing.
I want my three wishes.

01:04:43.630 --> 01:04:46.408
Three wishes? Morty.
No. You're screwing it all up.

01:04:46.508 --> 01:04:49.536
Don't worry about it.
We'll all get what we want.

01:04:49.636 --> 01:04:52.497
- LEPRECHAUN: Open this door.
- Not yet.

01:04:52.597 --> 01:04:53.873
Not till I get my wishes.

01:04:53.973 --> 01:04:57.377
Now, I could ask you
for a million dollars.

01:04:57.477 --> 01:04:59.546
Even a billion dollars, but no.

01:04:59.646 --> 01:05:03.842
What I think I would like
is your crummy pot of gold.

01:05:03.942 --> 01:05:06.761
Morty. God! Stop it!

01:05:06.861 --> 01:05:10.849
You hear me in there?
I want your gold.

01:05:10.949 --> 01:05:13.059
Morty, don't do it.
Let me out of here.

01:05:13.159 --> 01:05:16.771
LEPRECHAUN: Oh. It's a
greedy man I'm dealing with.

01:05:16.871 --> 01:05:19.607
- Don't.
- LEPRECHAUN: Are you sure you want it?

01:05:19.707 --> 01:05:23.862
Oh, I'm sure. My first
wish is for your gold.

01:05:23.962 --> 01:05:25.839
So be it.

01:05:28.174 --> 01:05:29.784
Where is it?

01:05:29.884 --> 01:05:32.182
Oh, it's coming.

01:05:34.556 --> 01:05:36.103
(GROANS)

01:05:36.391 --> 01:05:38.234
(COINS DROPPING)

01:05:42.772 --> 01:05:44.273
(GROANS)

01:05:45.942 --> 01:05:49.429
Get it out. Get it out of me.

01:05:49.529 --> 01:05:53.516
Oh, God. Morty! Morty, no!

01:05:53.616 --> 01:05:57.270
Get it out. Get it out of me.

01:05:57.370 --> 01:06:00.899
LEPRECHAUN: I could do it, but you
have to let me out of the safe first.

01:06:00.999 --> 01:06:02.942
Do you wish me out of the safe?

01:06:03.042 --> 01:06:07.547
Yes, God damn it.
I wish you out of the safe.

01:06:09.466 --> 01:06:11.493
Where the hell are you?

01:06:11.593 --> 01:06:15.789
LEPRECHAUN: You'll have to open
the door. It's wrought iron, remember?

01:06:15.889 --> 01:06:17.891
Didn't you read the book?

01:06:19.559 --> 01:06:20.710
(GROANING)

01:06:20.810 --> 01:06:23.563
CODY: Stop it, Morty!

01:06:25.231 --> 01:06:27.074
Morty, stop it!

01:06:38.578 --> 01:06:41.297
Your second wish has been granted.

01:06:41.748 --> 01:06:44.943
Get it out. Get it out!

01:06:45.043 --> 01:06:47.921
Ah! You see,
you shouldn't be so greedy.

01:06:48.755 --> 01:06:51.908
Get it out of me! Get it out!

01:06:52.008 --> 01:06:54.244
So, uh, is that your wish?

01:06:54.344 --> 01:06:57.768
Yes, yes, yes.

01:06:57.972 --> 01:07:00.750
I wish you to get it out of me.

01:07:00.850 --> 01:07:03.273
Very well.

01:07:03.937 --> 01:07:05.438
Ahhh!

01:07:06.731 --> 01:07:08.778
Morty, no!

01:07:09.651 --> 01:07:11.152
(GRUNTING)

01:07:23.289 --> 01:07:24.691
A-ha!

01:07:24.791 --> 01:07:27.168
I missed you.

01:07:33.967 --> 01:07:35.810
Help me.

01:07:36.386 --> 01:07:39.038
Love to, friend.
But you're all out of wishes.

01:07:39.138 --> 01:07:40.639
(GLASS SHATTERING)

01:07:52.402 --> 01:07:55.263
Morty, come on, man.

01:07:55.363 --> 01:07:56.556
Why'd you do it?

01:07:56.656 --> 01:08:00.035
No! No! Morty, no!

01:08:05.123 --> 01:08:07.734
All right, you little bastard.
Come and get me.

01:08:07.834 --> 01:08:11.554
Drop that weapon, psycho, and get up.

01:08:13.089 --> 01:08:15.241
How many more people
have you killed tonight?

01:08:15.341 --> 01:08:17.827
- What are you talking about?
- I know who you are.

01:08:17.926 --> 01:08:20.705
I saw you in the news.
Whole town is looking for you.

01:08:20.805 --> 01:08:22.852
Put your hands up.

01:08:23.474 --> 01:08:25.725
And move out slowly.

01:08:28.854 --> 01:08:30.506
Don't try anything funny.
I'm taking you in.

01:08:30.607 --> 01:08:32.591
GIRL: Help. Help me, please.

01:08:32.692 --> 01:08:34.594
- It's a trick. Don't...
- Shut up!

01:08:34.694 --> 01:08:37.095
What kind of spree are you on, sicko?

01:08:37.196 --> 01:08:39.890
- No, it's the...
- I'm not afraid to use this.

01:08:39.991 --> 01:08:41.600
Now take me to her now.

01:08:41.701 --> 01:08:43.435
GIRL: Please, help me.

01:08:43.536 --> 01:08:45.313
(IN GIRL'S VOICE)
The boy has hurt me.

01:08:45.412 --> 01:08:47.064
We're coming, ma'am.

01:08:47.165 --> 01:08:48.666
(LAUGHS)

01:08:49.459 --> 01:08:53.087
- Listen to me. Call for backup.
- Shut up.

01:08:54.589 --> 01:08:55.948
Freeze!

01:08:56.049 --> 01:08:57.550
(ENGINE RUNNING)

01:09:07.310 --> 01:09:08.877
What is this? Some kind of trick?

01:09:08.978 --> 01:09:11.339
You'll not be taking
the boy anywhere.

01:09:11.439 --> 01:09:13.466
I'll have my gold.

01:09:13.566 --> 01:09:15.693
- (LAUGHS)
- (TIRES SCREECHING)

01:09:25.662 --> 01:09:27.334
Ha! You missed me!

01:09:39.716 --> 01:09:40.993
No!

01:09:41.094 --> 01:09:42.595
(LAUGHS)

01:09:53.898 --> 01:09:56.843
I want my coin. Give it to me.

01:09:56.943 --> 01:09:59.887
I'm not giving you anything
until I get Bridget.

01:09:59.987 --> 01:10:02.849
You're gonna have to kill me if you
want your stinkin' piece of gold.

01:10:02.949 --> 01:10:04.826
So be it.

01:10:05.034 --> 01:10:06.535
(LAUGHING)

01:10:06.828 --> 01:10:08.454
(TIRES SCREECHING)

01:10:08.955 --> 01:10:10.456
(SCREAMS)

01:10:17.296 --> 01:10:18.698
I'm not dead.

01:10:18.798 --> 01:10:21.642
You will be if you
don't give me my coin.

01:10:22.218 --> 01:10:24.641
You can't do it, can you?

01:10:27.807 --> 01:10:29.809
As long as I have this.

01:10:30.309 --> 01:10:32.211
You have to give it to me.

01:10:32.311 --> 01:10:35.405
You want it? Come get it.

01:10:59.005 --> 01:11:01.724
I'm gonna save Bridget!

01:11:01.924 --> 01:11:04.426
And then I'm gonna get you!

01:11:05.094 --> 01:11:07.642
You can't hide from me!

01:11:08.598 --> 01:11:11.226
I know where you live!

01:11:17.982 --> 01:11:20.576
Have you had your iron today?

01:11:27.366 --> 01:11:29.602
I'll be waiting. (LAUGHS)

01:11:29.702 --> 01:11:33.581
A leprechaun's home
has many surprises.

01:11:36.417 --> 01:11:40.262
Sweetie, still playing games?

01:11:40.379 --> 01:11:44.008
Come out. We may be having
a house guest soon.

01:11:44.300 --> 01:11:46.347
Where have you been?

01:11:46.803 --> 01:11:49.101
I've been so lonely.

01:11:49.806 --> 01:11:52.809
How could you leave a bride
on her wedding night?

01:11:54.227 --> 01:11:57.296
Later, my dear. I have to
prepare for our visitor.

01:11:57.396 --> 01:12:01.050
What visitor could be
more important than me?

01:12:01.150 --> 01:12:05.371
After all, I thought you
waited a thousand years.

01:12:07.740 --> 01:12:10.038
- (BRIDGET CHUCKLES)
- That I have.

01:12:11.536 --> 01:12:14.585
It's been a long millennium
for the leprechaun.

01:12:14.705 --> 01:12:17.400
He's had no one to
care for his needs.

01:12:17.500 --> 01:12:18.985
BRIDGET: Oh!

01:12:19.085 --> 01:12:21.178
Well, that's what I'm here for.

01:12:22.505 --> 01:12:24.574
To give you what you...

01:12:24.674 --> 01:12:26.721
Deserve!

01:12:28.427 --> 01:12:30.496
My favorite awl.

01:12:30.596 --> 01:12:34.350
My dad gave that to me and
you've gone and broke it.

01:12:35.268 --> 01:12:37.128
- Now you're in for some trouble.
- (CAR APPROACHING)

01:12:37.228 --> 01:12:39.196
Please!

01:12:40.231 --> 01:12:41.466
Ah.

01:12:41.566 --> 01:12:43.989
Sounds like our guest has arrived.

01:12:46.237 --> 01:12:48.284
Don't go anywhere.

01:13:28.404 --> 01:13:30.076
Bridget?

01:13:33.784 --> 01:13:35.627
Bridget?

01:13:36.662 --> 01:13:38.163
(STRUGGLING)

01:13:45.212 --> 01:13:47.259
Bridget?

01:13:52.219 --> 01:13:53.720
(GASPS)

01:13:58.017 --> 01:14:00.064
Oh, God!

01:14:00.603 --> 01:14:01.587
(EXCLAIMS)

01:14:01.687 --> 01:14:03.923
A little lost, are you?

01:14:04.023 --> 01:14:05.524
(STRUGGLING)

01:14:18.955 --> 01:14:20.456
(GASPS)

01:14:21.248 --> 01:14:23.716
What a clich.

01:14:23.876 --> 01:14:25.377
(GROWLS)

01:14:26.545 --> 01:14:28.547
Give me the coin.

01:14:30.383 --> 01:14:32.726
The coin.

01:14:34.553 --> 01:14:36.555
(BRIDGET GROANING)

01:14:39.642 --> 01:14:41.143
(COUGHING)

01:14:41.978 --> 01:14:44.071
SKELETON: Hand it over.

01:14:46.899 --> 01:14:48.776
The coin!

01:14:50.403 --> 01:14:51.596
(CODY GRUNTS)

01:14:51.696 --> 01:14:53.197
(SKELETON GRUNTS)

01:14:54.740 --> 01:14:56.662
Come on, son.

01:15:10.047 --> 01:15:11.548
(GRUNTS)

01:15:12.133 --> 01:15:14.201
Give it to me. Get the coin.

01:15:14.301 --> 01:15:16.269
SKELETON: I'm trying, master.

01:15:28.482 --> 01:15:30.279
(LEPRECHAUN LAUGHS)

01:15:31.444 --> 01:15:33.241
(SKELETON WHEEZING)

01:15:52.882 --> 01:15:54.383
(GRUNTS)

01:16:09.315 --> 01:16:11.317
Bridget?

01:16:13.778 --> 01:16:15.996
Where are you?

01:16:16.447 --> 01:16:17.948
Whoa!

01:16:19.450 --> 01:16:20.951
Ahhh!

01:16:22.870 --> 01:16:25.498
Give up the coin, lad,
and I'll set you free.

01:16:27.124 --> 01:16:29.342
No!

01:16:44.350 --> 01:16:46.002
- Bridget!
- Cody!

01:16:46.102 --> 01:16:48.587
Are you all right.
What has he done to you?

01:16:48.687 --> 01:16:50.780
Surprise!

01:16:51.357 --> 01:16:53.467
Don't take another step.

01:16:53.567 --> 01:16:55.177
Cody, run! Get out of here.

01:16:55.277 --> 01:16:57.905
- I'm not leaving without you!
- Go!

01:17:00.032 --> 01:17:02.059
What will you do now, Cody?

01:17:02.159 --> 01:17:05.583
You think you can beat
me here in my home?

01:17:06.789 --> 01:17:10.759
Take your damn ring back,
I don't want it anymore.

01:17:11.001 --> 01:17:12.878
Run!

01:17:17.633 --> 01:17:20.244
A game of hide and seek. How lovely.

01:17:20.344 --> 01:17:21.845
(LAUGHS)

01:17:25.850 --> 01:17:28.398
You know you won't get out.

01:17:33.399 --> 01:17:34.991
(CACKLING)

01:17:43.450 --> 01:17:44.477
- (GASPS)
- Shh!

01:17:44.577 --> 01:17:47.146
Don't scream. He'll hear us.
Come on. We got to find a way out.

01:17:47.246 --> 01:17:50.875
- Cody, I've tried.
- We'll do it together. Now come on.

01:17:51.208 --> 01:17:53.460
That's what you think.

01:18:04.305 --> 01:18:05.498
We're right back where we started.

01:18:05.598 --> 01:18:07.458
There's got to be a way out of here.

01:18:07.558 --> 01:18:09.526
Let's try this one.

01:18:17.693 --> 01:18:19.345
Dj vu.

01:18:19.445 --> 01:18:20.946
Ah.

01:18:21.405 --> 01:18:23.202
Let's try this one.

01:18:32.458 --> 01:18:34.631
What are we gonna do?

01:18:35.336 --> 01:18:37.133
I got an idea.

01:18:45.304 --> 01:18:46.914
Bridget?

01:18:47.014 --> 01:18:49.141
Bridget!

01:18:56.315 --> 01:18:57.716
Bridget!

01:18:57.816 --> 01:18:59.385
Ah! Are you all right?

01:18:59.485 --> 01:19:01.554
I saw him. I saw the leprechaun.

01:19:01.654 --> 01:19:03.264
- Where is he?
- He's back in the tunnels.

01:19:03.364 --> 01:19:06.016
I managed to get away. Come on.
You're not gonna believe this.

01:19:06.116 --> 01:19:07.518
But I actually found
a way out of here.

01:19:07.618 --> 01:19:09.854
- Well, let's go.
- Wait. Do you still have the coin?

01:19:09.954 --> 01:19:10.938
Yeah. Why?

01:19:11.038 --> 01:19:13.440
Leave the damn thing here.
That's all he wants.

01:19:13.540 --> 01:19:15.442
But, Bridget, as long as we have
the coin, he can't hurt us.

01:19:15.542 --> 01:19:17.736
- We're dead without the coin.
- No. Listen to me, Cody.

01:19:17.836 --> 01:19:20.573
If leaving the coin keeps
that creep from following us,

01:19:20.673 --> 01:19:22.158
we've got to do it.

01:19:22.258 --> 01:19:25.202
- But...
- No. I know it's scary.

01:19:25.302 --> 01:19:27.554
It'll be okay.

01:19:28.013 --> 01:19:33.019
Give me the coin and let's
get out of here, please.

01:19:33.852 --> 01:19:36.195
I love you, Cody.

01:19:54.540 --> 01:19:56.383
(BRIDGET LAUGHING)

01:20:03.215 --> 01:20:05.558
LEPRECHAUN: You lose. (LAUGHS)

01:20:11.932 --> 01:20:15.606
I fooled you. Now there's
nothing to protect you.

01:20:16.061 --> 01:20:20.090
I have the gold coin and
there's no stopping me now.

01:20:20.190 --> 01:20:22.384
You can't outsmart a genius.

01:20:22.484 --> 01:20:24.327
Where's Bridget?

01:20:25.571 --> 01:20:27.514
Don't hurt him.

01:20:27.614 --> 01:20:30.309
- I'll go with you.
- Yes, you will.

01:20:30.409 --> 01:20:34.897
But first it's time to finish this
annoying boy off once and for all.

01:20:34.997 --> 01:20:36.874
Like hell.

01:20:40.461 --> 01:20:43.305
BRIDGET: Cody! No!

01:20:43.464 --> 01:20:45.932
Cody, no!

01:20:47.676 --> 01:20:49.678
He's dead?

01:20:56.560 --> 01:20:58.587
It's over?

01:20:58.687 --> 01:21:00.860
It's really over?

01:21:02.274 --> 01:21:05.552
Cry as you may. Cry as you might.

01:21:05.652 --> 01:21:08.530
It's gonna be one hell
of a wedding night.

01:21:10.949 --> 01:21:12.951
In your dreams.

01:21:17.206 --> 01:21:18.707
Ahhh!

01:21:19.375 --> 01:21:21.735
Real milk chocolate, genius.

01:21:21.835 --> 01:21:23.336
Ahhh!

01:21:28.467 --> 01:21:30.469
He's gonna blow.

01:21:35.891 --> 01:21:37.392
(ENERGY CRACKLING)

01:21:45.317 --> 01:21:46.989
(BIRDS CHIRPING)

01:21:50.489 --> 01:21:53.809
How did you know it wasn't me
you gave the coin to before?

01:21:53.909 --> 01:21:55.831
He kisses differently than you.

01:22:00.833 --> 01:22:03.235
Whose kiss you like better?

01:22:03.335 --> 01:22:04.903
I'll have to think about it.

01:22:05.003 --> 01:22:06.504
(BOTH LAUGH)

01:22:09.049 --> 01:22:10.675
BRIDGET: Are you gonna keep it?

01:22:10.676 --> 01:22:12.849
Trust me, it's not worth it.

